JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has congratulated his Chinese counterpart, Xi Jinping, on his re-election. In a statement, the president says he’s confident bilateral relations between the countries will continue to grow. READ: China's Xi gets second term with powerful ally as VP China’s lawmakers unanimously re-elected Xi Jinping in a vote on Saturday. The Chinese leader is to visit South Africa in July as the country hosts the 10th BRICS summit. eNCA